Great Chinese style chow mein! This place is Americanized Chinese food. I have been here a few times now and keep coming back. I wish I could give 4.5 stars because some of the stuff is really good and the prices are great. $7-$8 for most dishes, It is easy to feed a family of five for $25 because they give so much food.

The only critique is the breading on the chicken wings and shrimp. That is the reason for 4.5 stars instead of 5. It's sub par.<//Text>

< text>
Sold a hefty sum of vintage Pokemon cards to the folks at Core TCG and it was an overwhelmingly positive experience. Their buy list pricing on most cards was on the higher end vs other sites. When the cards arrived, they processed and submitted the buy offer within less than 1 full business day. Their revised buy offer was extremely fair and the only cards they submitted revised pricing on were cards that I was completely expecting. They deposited the money into my Paypal almost instantaneously. Having never received money in PayPal, I had PayPayl security issues accepting the money and Core TCG went above and beyond (after the fact) to take some extra steps to verify the transer and ensure I got my money quickly. I was really nervous about this process having held onto these cards for 20+ years but Core TCG made the process communicative, reassuring, and pleasant. My only complaint; I wish their buy list was bigger so I could do more business with them!<//text>

Sold my cards to them in two orders. I submitted one buylist, then found extra cards the next day so I submitted a second one. Both lists were approved around the same time, so I sent both orders in the same mail package, but in separate deck boxes. One of the orders was processed and the other was "lost" despite them both being shipped in the same package.

Great company if you want to pay someone to steal your cards and blame you for losing them.</Review>

<Rating>4<//Rating>< Text>
I live in Killeen and tried to arrive an hour early to the event in Dallas that was held on 10/20/2018 but due to traffic and parking issues i was late to the event. When i arrived i was 45 minutes late and spoke to two gentlemen at the Registration table. Ken Watkins informed me that i was too late to play in the event and that i would not receive my entry packs paid for by my online preregistration. He told me that i would receive a full refund sometime within the next week. I should have been able to still play in the event with a Round 1 loss and receive my entry packs that i had already paid for but that was not the case.

UPDATE: the company owner, Chris, contacted me and gave me a full refund for the pre registration. He also decided to send me all of the product I would have gotten should I have been allowed to play in the tournament. He snuck in an extra playmat as well so i am updating this review from 2 stars to 4 stars for good customer service.</Text>

< text>
Easy to moderate hike with plenty of vistas along the way.  Midway through the hike is a tree-shrouded Canyon that offers a relaxing and tranquil experience before the steepest part of the ascent to the point where all your effort is  rewarded with  spectacular views of the sweeping costal mountain range, Santa Barbara, Pacific Ocean and the Channel Islands.< /text>

< text>
A great lookout point over Santa Barbara. The hike wasn't to long or to difficult. Better to go in the morning when the weather is cooler since a majority of the hike is uphill and it can be very hot in the summer. Overall, a great hiking trail and great scenery.<//text>

Awesome hike from Stevens Park up Jesusita Trail all the way to the point. About 18,000 steps ! Great view of the entire SB area.  Can get chilly up there if day is overcast and towards afternoon. Bring some water and a camera.  Cheers !< /Review>

<Name>Cathy Stanfill</Name><date>1528986634917</date>< Review>
This is the best American buffet chain (I am not counting the countless casino buffets - that's a total other category). For the food choices available the quality is there and that is the most important. I was very pleased with my mac 'n cheese, and other food choices that I put on my plate. And the dessert was GOOD. I am very happy that Golden Corral finally made it to California. (Many years ago I was introduced to the Golden Corral while on a trip to Oklahoma and was very impressed).<//Review>

<user>114562239536100465083< /user><user_name>Israel<//user_name><time>1544590210550<//time><rate>4</rate>< text>
Great food for the price.  What can I say. It's buffet food.  But!  They have steak.  Just Ask for as rare cook as they will give you and it's pretty tender.  Now I wish they had A1 instead of what I call fake1 sauce. Lots of choices, not as many as the other Golden Corrals.  This place is a converted location from an old hometown buffet.   I would defendsdef recommend this place.  The people are super friendly my stake was cooked to my liking ..  even some restaurants won't do that for you.  So I will come here when ever I can.< /text>

This is the best American buffet chain (I am not counting the countless casino buffets - that's a total other category). For the food choices available the quality is there and that is the most important. I was very pleased with my mac 'n cheese, and other food choices that I put on my plate. And the dessert was GOOD. Christine Dey</username>
< text>
Actually pretty good for a buffet.  Those aren't always great, you never know what you'll get and aren't always great quality.  This is mainly good, tasty food.  Lots of choices.  Hot, fried, salad, dessert, international... all kinds of foods to be found.  Pricey, so come hungry.  Chocolate fountain and cotton candy too!  We'll go again, but not often.  Pricey and not healthy.  Although there are plenty of choices if you want to go a more healthy route.< /text>

< time>
1521609196467<//time>
<Text>**Enter the parking from Lincoln. The Golden Corral sign you see off of State College is the back of the restaurant! You'd have to walk all the way around to the front if you park off State College.**

Come expecting a hometown buffet and be blown away! Prices are a bit more expensive, but it's worth it. Came on a Tuesday at 5:30pm and there was no line. It was about $100 for 5 adults, 1 child, and 2 beverages. ($16.29 per adult) The beverages are self service, but the waiters and waitresses offer to refill your drinks for you constantly. You can even order milk, chocolate milk, or a hot cocoa packet through the servers. Our waitress was Alicia and she was awesome! She cleared plates quickly and offered to refill drinks even though our table was next to the soda fountain. On to the food. The buffet setup is the same as the hometown buffet they took over. They had a taco station but I didn't feel like waiting in line for it. I really enjoyed the prime rib. It's rare when they slice it, so ask for them to cook it for you before they place it on your plate. Everything else I tried was good too, but my favorite was the prime rib. They also have a large variety of desserts! I like how they have the skewers in the strawberries, pineapple, marshmallows, and rice krispies so your hands don't tough them before placing in the chocolate fountain. It's definitely more sanitary. They also have cotton candy and thrifty ice cream (chocolate, vanilla, strawberry, and rainbow sherbet)!  Make sure you hand a bowl over to whoever's scooping ice cream. There's cakes, pie, cupcakes, cookies, jello, pudding, soft serve, and delicious gummy bears as well! Such a great way to end our meal. I would return for the variety of food and the excellent service.< /Text>< Rating>
5<//Rating>

For ~$17 you get a pretty good quality buffet experience. It is right up there with the above average buffets you would find in Vegas. < Review>
Admittedly when my party members suggested we go to a buffet my immediate reaponse was " nope!" The covid situation didnt seem to shine a great light on a place where everyone digs into the same platter. But they pushed and I relented. I was pleasantly surprised. < review>
I loved it. I was hesitant to take my party of 16 to a buffet but with ages from 1 - 86, I needed some options. Golden Corral did the trick. We were with a disabled family member and they were quick to offer a chair without our asking and we were seated within 15 minutes or less. My party was easily accommodated with two  tables, which was expected. I cannot complain. The food choices were awesome and of course there was plenty of turkey and ham. I was even surprised to see a steak grill, and those steaks were amazing! The kids ate well too and then enjoyed a variety of desserts and some cotton candy. I am so glad that we enjoyed a meal together at Golden Corral. If there was any room for improvement, it would be the parking and handicap parking. It was located in a Target and strip mall lot and could use some elbow room and some more handicap spaces. Just don't let that stop you from enjoying family, friends and a variety of delicious food. Enjoy!</review>

<rate>4<//rate>< Text>
I've seen the TV add for years, but one was never close enough to me to give them a try. Well a little over a year ago, one finally came to town, and while it took me awhile to get there, I was glad I did. So first thing, I went for dinner, and it was a little over $16 without a drink. However, for that price you get a huge selection of different offerings from 3 different flavors of chicken wings, to ribs, to Steak cooked to order. There's roasted chicken, and fried chicken, baked tilapia, pulled pork, and tons of side options and choices for the non-carnivores (that means vegetarians and vegans).

Now, this is not a classy restaurant, so you don't go here for the ambiance. However, considering what this place is, a low-cost buffet, I have to admit I was surprised by how good the food tasted. I got several of their dessert selections (sundae, apple pie, peach cobbler, boysenberry pie) and most were good. I will be back, but at $16 a person, this will not be a regular dining option.<//Text>

<time>1535642956372< /time><Name>Jason Weller< /Name><Text>I've seen the TV add for years, but one was never close enough to me to give them a try. Well a little over a year ago, one finally came to town, and while it took me awhile to get there, I was glad I did. So first thing, I went for dinner, and it was a little over $16 without a drink. However, for that price you get a huge selection of different offerings from 3 different flavors of chicken wings, to ribs, to Steak cooked to order. There's roasted chicken, and fried chicken, baked tilapia, pulled pork, and tons of side options and choices for the non-carnivores (that means vegetarians and vegans).

Now, this is not a classy restaurant, so you don't go here for the ambiance. However, considering what this place is, a low-cost buffet, I have to admit I was surprised by how good the food tasted. I got several of their dessert selections (sundae, apple pie, peach cobbler, boysenberry pie) and most were good. I will be back, but at $16 a person, this will not be a regular dining option.</Text><user>109890307279432171560</user>< Response>

<name>Tee A.< /name><Time>1540424156675<//Time><rating>5<//rating>< review>
As a long-time customer of Golden Corral restaurant chain, I have high expectations when I walk in the door of any location. You see, I once lived within a few miles of the number one Golden Corral restaurant in the entire country! (It was ranked number one at least 3 years in a row! Sorry, but that was in another state).

I must admit on my first couple of visits here in Anaheim, I had some concerns. They are at a slight disadvantage being that they used to be a HomeTown Buffet. This location did not have the luxury of getting the full "GC makeover". It still looks like  HomeTown Buffet on the inside.

I must admit that the food quality here is improving. Now when I go, I do feel like I'm at a Golden Corral. They also do a great job in keeping the food bar well-stocked.

The associates are very friendly and eager to help, even if you're not at one of their tables!
The true test will be Sunday brunch..... can't wait to experience that here in Anaheim.

I have not met the manager yet. But from what I can see, he is hustling to make it a great restaurant. I hope he will press forward and make it work. This is an ideal location because of the shopping center that it's in....
Lots of potential customers here.</review>
